transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm going to pull up your account with your telephone number. I'm going to read off your—

Speaker 2: Chart.

Speaker 1: Just help me verify some things so I can help you put a stop to this, all right, bud?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, just stand by.

Speaker 2: Let me just pull this up.

Speaker 1: Were you on hold for some time?

Speaker 2: We're getting a lot of orders for some bills, but nevertheless, I do see that you're working—

Speaker 1: This correctly with Victoria, Dr. Victoria Monk.

Speaker 2: First time I've ever seen her name up, but she is one of our Pfizer doctors, and it looks—

Speaker 1: Like she set you up with a VIP status, and she wrote a prescription for the ADV Viagra—

Speaker 2: 50 milligrams.

Speaker 1: It's a white diamond pill, it's FDA approved, it's a Pfizer one, the one we make in our—

Speaker 2: Pfizer labs in France, but I also see that she ordered the pharmacy to send you refills—

Speaker 1: On her behalf.

Speaker 2: Do you want me to put a stop to this?

Speaker 1: You're not getting it on monthly anymore?

Speaker 2: Well, I was just going to cancel it just because I'm trying to save some money, so just wanted—

Speaker 1: Any unneeded expenses I'm trying to cut just because we're trying to save up.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I know, and it's not how much you make, bud, it's how much you save, and we're around—

Speaker 1: The same age.

Speaker 2: I get it.

Speaker 1: We're living 20 cents a dollar.

Speaker 2: We're here in Brentwood, Beverly Hills, so I know what you mean.

Speaker 1: I feel like it's so expensive here in L.A., and yeah, I'll take care of you, bud.

Speaker 2: I'll set it up so when you're ready, you can click a button if you need more, but I'll—

Speaker 1: Definitely put a stop to any monthly refills and any charges, all right?

Speaker 2: So, hold your line.

Speaker 1: Okay, no, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course, but thanks for being candid and speaking up and letting us know how we—

Speaker 1: Can help you, all right?

Speaker 2: Stand by.

Speaker 1: Okay.
